io.pivotal.rti.protocols

Class AbstractProtocolAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.pivotal.rti.protocols.AbstractProtocolAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProtocolAdapter, ProtocolMetricManager

    public abstract class AbstractProtocolAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProtocolAdapter, ProtocolMetricManager
    Default implementation for protocols SDK contract ProtocolAdapter Implementers of new protocol adapters are encouraged to extend this class and override the abstract methods in it, primarily bytesToProtocolEvent(byte[]) In addition to implement the SDK contract, this class also provides hooks into JMX metrics and other error handling. Those are the reasons, why implementers are recommended to extend this class.

      • bytesToProtocolEvent

        public abstract java.util.Collection<ProtocolEvent> bytesToProtocolEvent(byte[] buffer)
                                                                  throws java.io.IOException
        This is an abstract method that all implementers are expected to override. This is where the implementation details for how raw bytes of data can be converted to meaningful ProtocolEvent RTI does not restrict how this implementation should be done. Users are free to use special codecs or other libraries to convert the byte array into ProtocolEvent.
        Parameters:
        buffer - byte array that is used for transforming to a list of ProtocolEvents
        Returns:
        List of ProtocolEvents
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
